---------------------------------------------------
-- Mekanism Fission Reactor Monitoring Program   --
-- Created for CC:Tweaked and Mekanism           --
-- Originally created by InternetUnexplorer on   --
-- GitHub. Modified for personal use, by         --
-- iPlay_G on Minecraft, Derrick355 on GitHub.   --
-- As the original program did not contain any   --
-- license, this will not contain any license.   --
-- However, this software is provided "AS-IS",   --
-- with NO WARRANTY of ANY kind. There is no     --
-- guarentee of fitness for a particular         --
-- purpose.                                      --
-- Feel free to use it, but I, nor the           --
-- original author are responsible for any       --
-- issues arising from the use of this program.  --
--                    -=@=-                      --
-- Thank you for downloading this program.       --
---------------------------------------------------


--- NOTES ---
-- If you see 'CRITICAL' on your monitor as the 
-- state, that is OK. Critical is what real 
-- reactors are considered when operating normally.

-- It is generally recommended to edit settings
-- in an IDE or text editor for ease of use.

-- It is assumed you have a 6 wide, 4 tall monitor
-- attached via a modem.

-- References to an analog lever are common, since
-- I used the Create mod, however if you don't
-- have it, any way to input a variable-power
-- redstone signal should work.

-- Binary levers are just vanillia levers.


--- RECOMMENDED & ASSUMED COMPUTER I/O SETUP ---
-- TOP: Binary lever, used to enable/disable manual burn rate control
-- LEFT: Analog lever, used as coarse adjust on burn control
-- RIGHT: Analog lever, used as fine adjust on burn control
-- BOTTOM: Binary lever, used as reactor on/off control
-- BACK: Modem to connect to reactor, turbine, and monitor
-- FRONT: Alarm or siren. Outputs a redstone signal if turbine power falls below a set threshold.


--- VARIABLE SETTINGS ---
-- Set the multiplier for the burn rate coarse setting.
-- Default = 75
burn_rate_coarse_multi = 75

-- Set the multiplier for the burn rate fine setting.
-- Default = 5
burn_rate_fine_multi = 5

-- Maximum auto burn rate to establish
-- Default = 120
burn_rate_auto_max = 120

-- What turbine power percent value should burn rate be max at?
-- For this value and all lower, burn rate will be at the max defined above.
-- Default = 0.5 (for 50%)
min_turbine_power = 0.50

-- What turbine power percent value should burn rate be zero at?
-- For this value and all higher, burn rate will be at zero.
-- Default = 0.75 (for 75%)
max_turbine_power = 0.75

-- What value should the alarm go off if turbine power falls below?
-- Default = 0.46
turbine_min_power = 0.46

-- What is the monitor called on the network?
-- Default = monitor_0
monitor_name = "monitor_2"

-- Are you playing on a server with Advanced peripherals?
-- This is used so that if a server is restarting the computer can
-- shot down the reactor. Note, the server must issue some kind of
-- restart warning beforehand.
-- Default = true
on_server = true

-- If the above is true, you must configure this line.
-- What message in chat should the program look for to see if the server
-- is restarting?
-- Default = "SCRAM"
restart_message = "SCRAM"

-- Do not modify anything past this line unless you know what you are doing.

------------------------------------------------

local state, data, reactor, turbine, info_window, rules_window

local STATES = {
	READY = 1, -- Reactor is off and can be started with the lever
	RUNNING = 2, -- Reactor is running and all rules are met
	ESTOP = 3, -- Reactor is stopped due to rule(s) being violated
	UNKNOWN = 4, -- Reactor or turbine peripherals are missing
}

------------------------------------------------

local function check_for_restart_scram()
	if fs.exists("disk/scrammed") then
		incoming_restart = true
		fs.delete("disk/scrammed")
		fs.makeDir("disk/notify_restart")
	else
		incoming_restart = false
	end
	return incoming_restart
end

incoming_restart = check_for_restart_scram()

local function check_for_restart_notify()
	if fs.exists("disk/notify_restart") then
		notify_restart = true
		fs.delete("disk/notify_restart")
	else
		notify_restart = false
	end
	return notify_restart
end

notify_restart = check_for_restart_notify()

local function pollChatbox()
    while true do
        local box = peripheral.find('chatBox', function(_, chatbox) return chatbox.getOperationCooldown('chatMessage') == 0 end)
        if box then
            return box
        end
        sleep(0.1)
    end
end

------------------------------------------------

local rules = {}

local function add_rule(name, fn)
	table.insert(rules, function()
		local ok, rule_met, value = pcall(fn)
		if ok and value ~= false then
			return rule_met, string.format("%s ( %s)", name, value)
	elseif ok then
		return rule_met, string.format("%s (%s)", name, value)
		else
			return false, name
		end
	end)
end

add_rule("REACTOR TEMPERATURE      <=  1100K  ", function()
	local value = string.format("%3dK", math.ceil(data.reactor_temp))
	return data.reactor_temp <= 1100, value
end)

add_rule("REACTOR DAMAGE           <=    10%  ", function()
	local value = string.format("%3d%%", math.ceil(data.reactor_damage * 100))
	return data.reactor_damage <= 0.10, value
end)

add_rule("REACTOR COOLANT LEVEL    >=    95%  ", function()
	local value = string.format("%3d%%", math.floor(data.reactor_coolant * 100))
	return data.reactor_coolant >= 0.95, value
end)

add_rule("REACTOR WASTE LEVEL      <=    90%  ", function()
	local value = string.format("%3d%%", math.ceil(data.reactor_waste * 100))
	return data.reactor_waste <= 0.90, value
end)

add_rule("TURBINE ENERGY LEVEL     <=    95%  ", function()
	local value = string.format("%3d%%", math.ceil(data.turbine_energy * 100))
	return data.turbine_energy <= 0.95, value
end)

if on_server then
	add_rule("INCOMING SERVER RESTART  ==  FALSE  ", function()
		return not incoming_restart, notify_restart
	end)
end

local function all_rules_met()
	for i, rule in ipairs(rules) do
		if not rule() then
			return false
		end
	end
	-- Allow manual emergency stop with SCRAM button
	return state ~= STATES.RUNNING or data.reactor_on
end

------------------------------------------------

local function update_data()
	coarse_adjust = (tonumber(redstone.getAnalogInput("left")) * burn_rate_coarse_multi)
	fine_adjust = (tonumber(redstone.getAnalogInput("right")) * burn_rate_fine_multi)
	set_burn_rate = (coarse_adjust + fine_adjust)

	data = {
		lever_on = redstone.getInput("bottom"),
		burn_rate_limit = set_burn_rate,
		burn_rate_limited = redstone.getInput("top"),

		reactor_on = reactor.getStatus(),
		reactor_burn_rate = reactor.getBurnRate(),
		reactor_max_burn_rate = reactor.getMaxBurnRate(),
		reactor_temp = reactor.getTemperature(),
		reactor_damage = reactor.getDamagePercent(),
		reactor_coolant = reactor.getCoolantFilledPercentage(),
		reactor_waste = reactor.getWasteFilledPercentage(),

		turbine_energy = turbine.getEnergyFilledPercentage(),
		turbine_power = turbine.getEnergy(),
		turbine_power = turbine.getEnergy(),
		max_turbine_power = turbine.getMaxEnergy()
	}

end
------------------------------------------------

local monitor = peripheral.wrap(monitor_name)

term.redirect(monitor)

local function colored(text, fg, bg)
	term.setTextColor(fg or colors.white)
	term.setBackgroundColor(bg or colors.black)
	term.write(string.upper(text))
end

local function make_section(name, x, y, w, h, color)
	for row = 1, h do
		term.setCursorPos(x, y + row - 1)
		local char = (row == 1 or row == h) and "\127" or " "
		colored("\127" .. string.rep(char, w - 2) .. "\127", color or colors.gray)
	end

	term.setCursorPos(x + 2, y)
	colored(" " .. name .. " ")

	return window.create(term.current(), x + 2, y + 2, w - 4, h - 4)
end

local function update_info()
	local prev_term = term.redirect(info_window)

	term.clear()
	term.setCursorPos(1, 1)

	if state == STATES.UNKNOWN then
		colored("ERROR RETRIEVING DATA", colors.red)
		return
	end

	colored("REACTOR: ")
	colored(data.reactor_on and "CRITICAL" or "SHUTDOWN", data.reactor_on and colors.green or colors.red)
	colored(" LEVER: ")
	colored(data.lever_on and "POWERED" or "SECURED", data.lever_on and colors.green or colors.red)
	colored(" BURN RATE: ")
	if data.burn_rate_limited == false then
		colored(string.format("%4.1f", data.reactor_burn_rate), colors.blue)
	else
		colored(string.format("%4.1f", data.reactor_burn_rate), colors.yellow)
	end
	colored("/", colors.lightGray)
	colored(string.format("%4.0f", data.reactor_max_burn_rate), colors.blue)

	term.setCursorPos(34, 2)
	colored("SET LIMIT: ")
	if data.burn_rate_limited then
		colored(string.format("%4.1f", data.burn_rate_limit), colors.green)
	else
		colored(string.format("%4.1f", data.burn_rate_limit), colors.gray)
	end

	term.setCursorPos(1, 4)

	colored("STATUS: ")
	if state == STATES.READY then
		colored("READY - PULL LEVER TO STARTUP", colors.blue)
	elseif state == STATES.RUNNING then
		colored("RUNNING - PULL LEVER TO SHUTDOWN", colors.green)
	elseif state == STATES.ESTOP and not all_rules_met() then
		colored("SCRAM - SAFETY RULE VIOLATED", colors.red)
	elseif state == STATES.ESTOP then
		colored("SCRAM - TOGGLE LEVER TO RESET", colors.red)
	end -- STATES.UNKNOWN cases handled above

	term.setCursorPos(1, 6)
	
	colored("STORED POWER: ")
	colored(string.format("%4.0f", (data.turbine_power*4/1000000)), colors.green)
	colored(" MFE", colors.green)
	colored("/", colors.lightGray)

	colored(string.format("%4.0f", (data.max_turbine_power*4/1000000)), colors.blue)
	colored(" MFE", colors.blue)
	colored(" (")
	colored(string.format("%5.2f", (data.turbine_energy*100)), colors.green)
	colored("%", colors.green)
	colored(")")

	term.redirect(prev_term)
end


local estop_reasons = {}

local function update_rules()
	local prev_term = term.redirect(rules_window)

	term.clear()

	if state ~= STATES.ESTOP then
		estop_reasons = {}
	end

	for i, rule in ipairs(rules) do
		local ok, text = rule()
		term.setCursorPos(1, i)
		if ok and not estop_reasons[i] then
			colored("[ SAFE ] ", colors.green)
			colored(text, colors.lightGray)
		else
			colored("[ FAIL ] ", colors.red)
			colored(text, colors.red)
			estop_reasons[i] = true
		end
	end

	term.redirect(prev_term)
end

------------------------------------------------

local function main_loop()
	-- Search for peripherals again if one or both are missing
	if not state or state == STATES.UNKNOWN then
		reactor = peripheral.find("fissionReactorLogicAdapter")
		turbine = peripheral.find("turbineValve")
	end

	if not pcall(update_data) then
		-- Error getting data (either reactor or turbine is nil?)
		data = {}
		state = STATES.UNKNOWN
	elseif data.reactor_on == nil then
		-- Reactor is not connected
		state = STATES.UNKNOWN
	elseif data.turbine_energy == nil then
		-- Turbine is not connected
		state = STATES.UNKNOWN
	elseif not state then
		-- Program just started, get current state from lever
		state = data.lever_on and STATES.RUNNING or STATES.READY
	elseif state == STATES.READY and data.lever_on then
		-- READY -> RUNNING
		state = STATES.RUNNING
		-- Activate reactor
		incoming_restart = false
		pcall(reactor.activate)
		data.reactor_on = true
	elseif state == STATES.RUNNING and not data.lever_on then
		-- RUNNING -> READY
		state = STATES.READY
	elseif state == STATES.ESTOP and not data.lever_on then
		-- ESTOP -> READY
		state = STATES.READY
	elseif state == STATES.UNKNOWN then
		-- UNKNOWN -> ESTOP
		state = data.lever_on and STATES.ESTOP or STATES.READY
		estop_reasons = {}
	end

	-- Always enter ESTOP if safety rules are not met
	if state ~= STATES.UNKNOWN and not all_rules_met() then
		state = STATES.ESTOP
	end

	-- SCRAM reactor if not running
	if state ~= STATES.RUNNING and reactor then
		pcall(reactor.scram)
	end

	-- Make Windows
	local width = term.getSize()
	if state == STATES.ESTOP then
		window_color = colors.red
	elseif state == STATES.READY then
		window_color = colors.green
	else
		window_color = colors.gray
	end
	info_window = make_section("INFORMATION", 2, 2, width - 2, 10, window_color)
	rules_window = make_section("SAFETY RULES", 2, 13, width - 2, 13, window_color)

	-- Update info and rules windows
	pcall(update_info)
	pcall(update_rules)

	-- Update max burn rate to keep turbine below 75% energy.
	if state ~= STATES.UNKNOWN and data.burn_rate_limited == false then
	
		local tgt_burn_pct = math.min(math.max(0.0, 1 - (data.turbine_energy - min_turbine_power) / (max_turbine_power - min_turbine_power)), 1.0)
		pcall(reactor.setBurnRate, tgt_burn_pct * burn_rate_auto_max)
	elseif state ~= STATES.UNKNOWN and data.burn_rate_limited == true then
		pcall(reactor.setBurnRate, data.burn_rate_limit) -- Let burn rate be limited by an analog lever
	end 

	if data.turbine_energy < turbine_min_power then --Sound an alarm that's attached to the front of the computer if turbine power falls below 45%.
		redstone.setOutput("right", true)
	else
		redstone.setOutput("right", false)
	end
	sleep() -- Other calls should already yield, this is just in case
	return main_loop()
end

term.setPaletteColor(colors.black, 0x000000)
term.setPaletteColor(colors.gray, 0x343434)
term.setPaletteColor(colors.lightGray, 0xababab)
term.setPaletteColor(colors.red, 0xdb2d20)
term.setPaletteColor(colors.green, 0x01a252)
term.setPaletteColor(colors.blue, 0x01a0e4)
term.clear()


function scram_on_restart()
	chatBox = peripheral.find("chatBox")
	local event, username, message, uuid, isHidden = os.pullEvent("chat")
	pollChatbox().sendMessage("username: " .. username .. " message: `".. message .. "`")
	if message == restart_message then
		--fs.copy("/disk/scram.lua", "/disk/scrammed.lua")
		fs.makeDir("/disk/scrammed")
		pollChatbox().sendMessage("SCRAM aye")
	end
end

if on_server then
	parallel.waitForAny(main_loop, scram_on_restart)
else
	parallel.waitForAny(main_loop, function()
		os.pullEventRaw("terminate")
	end)
end

os.reboot()

content:
#!/bin/bash


# medidor de ping
# https://espanol.cox.com/residential/internet/guides/gaming-performance/ping-testing.html}

# Menos de 50 ms 'bueno'
# Menos de 100 ms 'regular'
# Menos de 150 ms 'malo'
# Mayor a 150 ms 'sin conexion'

# 1 True
# 0 False

host=$1

while :; do

    clear

    ping=$(ping -c 1 $host | grep "64 bytes from" | cut -d "=" -f 4 | cut -d " " -f 1)


    # si el valor es entero pasarlo a decimal.

    [[ "$ping" =~ .*$ ]] || ping=${ping}.0


    if [ $(awk 'BEGIN { if ('$ping' > 100.0) print 1; else print 0 }') -eq 1 ] &&  
        [ $(awk 'BEGIN { if ('$ping' <= 150.0) print 1; else print 0 }') -eq 1 ]; then

        echo "malo"

    elif [ $(awk 'BEGIN { if ('$ping' <= 50.0) print 1; else print 0 }') -eq 1 ]; then

        echo "bueno"

    elif [ $(awk 'BEGIN { if ('$ping' > 150.0) print 1; else print 0 }') -eq 1 ]; then

        echo "sin conexion"

    else
        echo "regular"
  
    fi

    sleep 0.5
done

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family={text:main font}:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<!--✻✻✻✻✻✻  npf audio player by @glenthemes  ✻✻✻✻✻✻-->
<script src="//tmblr-npf-audio.gitlab.io/s/init.js"></script>
<link href="//tmblr-npf-audio.gitlab.io/s/base.css" rel="stylesheet">
<script>
    tumblr_npf_audio({
        emptyTitleText: "Untitled track",
        emptyArtistText: "Untitled artist",
        emptyAlbumText: "Untitled album",
        
        titleLabel: "Track:",
        artistLabel: "Artist:",
        albumLabel: "Album:"
    });
</script>

<style edit-npf-audio-player>
.npf-audio-wrapper {
    --NPF-Audio-Buttons-Size: 1.4rem;
    --NPF-Audio-Buttons-Color: rgb(var(--question));
    --NPF-Audio-Buttons-Spacing: 1.3rem; 
    --NPF-Audio-Image-Size: 85px;
    --NPF-Audio-Image-Spacing: 0px;
}

.npf-audio-background {
    background-color: rgb(var(--question-background));
    border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));
    padding: 1.5rem;
}

.npf-audio-title-label,
.npf-audio-artist-label,
.npf-audio-album-label {
    font-weight: bold;
}

.npf-audio-title,
.npf-audio-artist,
.npf-audio-album {
    --NPF-Audio-Buttons-Color: rgb(var(--question)); 
}
</style>
    
<style type="text/css">

/* ===== CUSTOM PROPERTIES (DO NOT DELETE) ===== */

:root {
    --header-image: url({image:header image});
    --background-image: url({image:background});
    
    --background-repeat: {select:background-repeat};
    --font-size: {select:font size};
    --post-size: {select:Post Width};
    --body-font: '{text:main font}';
    --post-spacing: 1rem;
    --post-margins: 1rem;
    --caption-padding: 1rem;
}

:root, html[data-theme='light'] {
    --light-on: flex;
    --light-off: none;
    --background: {RGBcolor:background};
    --accent-one: {RGBcolor:accent};
    --accent-two: {RGBcolor:accent two};
    --accent-text: {RGBcolor:accent text};
    --accent-text-two: {RGBcolor:accent text};
    --text: {RGBcolor:text};
    --links: {RGBcolor:links};
    --link-hover: {RGBcolor:link hover};
    --primary: {RGBcolor:bold};
    --secondary: {RGBcolor:link hover};
    --posts: {RGBcolor:posts};
    --borders: {RGBcolor:border};
    --question: {RGBcolor:question};
    --question-background: {RGBcolor:question background};
    --audio-text: {RGBcolor:audio text};
    --audio-accent: {RGBcolor:audio accent};
    --audio-background: {RGBcolor:audio background};
    --permalink-like: {RGBcolor:permalink like};
    --permalink-reblog: {RGBcolor:permalink reblog};
}
html[data-theme='dark'] {
    --light-on: none;
    --light-off: flex;
    --background: {RGBcolor:background night};
    --accent-one: {RGBcolor:accent night};
    --accent-two: {RGBcolor:accent two night};
    --accent-text: {RGBcolor:accent text night};
    --accent-text-two: {RGBcolor:accent text night};
    --text: {RGBcolor:text night};
    --links: {RGBcolor:links night};
    --link-hover: {RGBcolor:link hover night};
    --primary: {RGBcolor:bold night};
    --secondary: {RGBcolor:link hover night};
    --posts: {RGBcolor:posts night};
    --borders: {RGBcolor:border night};
    --question: {RGBcolor:question night};
    --question-background: {RGBcolor:question background night};
    --audio-text: {RGBcolor:audio text};
    --audio-accent: {RGBcolor:audio accent};
    --audio-background: {RGBcolor:audio background};
    --permalink-like: {RGBcolor:permalink like};
    --permalink-reblog: {RGBcolor:permalink reblog};
}

/* ===== CSS RESETS ===== */

html.theme-transition,
html.theme-transition *,
html.theme-transition *:before,
html.theme-transition *:after {
  transition: 0s !important;
  transition-delay: 0 !important;
}
        
*,
*::before,
*::after {
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

* {
    margin: 0;
    font: inherit;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  html:focus-within {
   scroll-behavior: auto;
  }
  
 *,
 *::before,
 *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    scroll-behavior: auto !important;
  }
}

img, video {
    max-width: 100%;
    display: block;
}

input,
button,
textarea,
select {
    font: inherit;
}

html:focus-within {
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
}

/* ===== TUMBLR CONTROLS ===== */

iframe.tmblr-iframe {
    position:fixed!important;
    z-index: 300!important;
    top: 10px!important;
    right: 90px!important;
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
    transition: all 0.5s;
    transform:scale(0.7);
    transform-origin:100% 0;
}

body.controls-click iframe.tmblr-iframe {
    opacity: 1.0;
    visibility: visible;
    transition: all 0.5s;
}

html[data-theme='light'] iframe.tmblr-iframe {
    filter:invert(1);
    filter:invert(100%) hue-rotate(180deg);
}

html[data-theme='dark'] iframe.tmblr-iframe {
    opacity:1.0!important;
    filter:invert(0)!important;
    filter:invert(100%) hue-rotate(180deg);
}

/* ===== TUMBLR LIGHTBOX ===== */

.vignette, #vignette {
    opacity:0;
}
.lightbox-image, #tumblr_lightbox img {
    box-shadow:none!important;
    border-radius:0!important;
    max-width:none;
}
 
.tmblr-lightbox, #tumblr_lightbox {
    background-color: rgba(var(--background), 0.8)!important;
}
 
.lightbox-image, #tumblr_lightbox img {
    -moz-box-sizing:border-box;
    box-sizing:border-box;
}

/* ===== SCROLLBAR ===== */

::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 1rem;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
    background-color: rgb(var(--posts));
} 

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
    background-color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
    border-radius: 100vw;
    border: 4px solid rgb(var(--posts));
} 

/* ===== CUSTOM TEXT SELECTION ===== */

{block:ifCustomTextSelection}
::selection {
    background-color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
    color: rgb(var(--accent-two-text))
}
 
::-moz-selection {
    background-color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
    color: rgb(var(--accent-two-text))
}
 
::-webkit-selection {
    background-color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
    color: rgb(var(--accent-two-text))
}
{/block:ifCustomTextSelection}

/* ===== TOOLTIPS ===== */

.tippy-tooltip.custom-theme {
    background-color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
    color: rgb(var(--accent-text-two));
    text-align:center;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: lowercase;
}
 
.tippy-tooltip.custom-theme .tippy-svg-arrow {
  fill: rgb(var(--accent-two));
}

/* ===== BASIC STYLING ===== */

body {
    line-height: 1.6;
    background-color: rgb(var(--background));
    background-image: var(--background-image);
    background-repeat: var(--background-repeat);
    color: rgb(var(--text));
    {block:iffullbackground}
    background-size: cover;
    {/block:iffullbackground}
    background-attachment: fixed;
    font-family: var(--body-font), var(--font-sans);
    word-wrap: break-word;
    font-size: var(--font-size);
    text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    overflow-x: hidden;
}

b, strong {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-7);
    color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
}

i, em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
}

s, strike {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

a {
	text-decoration: none;
	color: rgb(var(--links));
	transition: 0.6s ease;
}

a:hover, a:focus {
    color: rgb(var(--secondary));
    transition: 0.6s ease;
}

p,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6 { overflow-wrap: break-word; }

h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6,h7 { font-weight: var(--font-weight-7); }

h1 { 
    font-size: var(--font-size-5); 
    line-height: 1.2;
}

h2 { font-size: var(--font-size-4); }

h3,h4,h5,h6,h7 { font-size: var(--font-size-3); }

.npf_color_joey     { color:#ff492f; } /* red */
.npf_color_monica   { color:#ff8a00; } /* orange */
.npf_color_ross     { color:#00cf35; } /* green */
.npf_color_rachel   { color:#00b8ff; } /* blue */
.npf_color_chandler { color:#973ff4; } /* purple */
.npf_color_niles    { color:#ff62ce; } /* pink */

figure.tmblr-full {  }  figure.tmblr-full img {        
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
}

blockquote {
    padding-left: var(--post-spacing);
	border-left: 2px solid rgb(var(--accent-two));
	margin: var(--post-spacing) 2.5rem;
}

blockquote:where(+ p) {
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
}

blockquote p {
    padding: 0!important;
}

figure.tmblr-full span.tmblr-alt-text-helper {
    margin-bottom: 2em!important;
}

a.read_more {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-7)
}

/* ===== UTILITY CLASSES ===== */

.all {
    min-height: 100vh;
    min-height: 100dvh;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
}

.flow > :where(:not(:first-child)) {
    margin-top: 0.8em;
}

.flex {
	display: flex;
	flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.centered {
	align-items: center;
	justify-content: center;
}

.align-center {
	align-items: center;
}

.justify-center {
	justify-content: center;
}

.sr-text {
	border: 0;
	clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);
	clip-path: inset(50%);
	height: 1px;
	margin: -1px;
	overflow: hidden;
	padding: 0;
	position: absolute;
	width: 1px;
	word-wrap: normal !important;
}

/* ===== POST CONTAINER ===== */

main {
	width: 100%;
	margin: auto;
	max-width: 1240px;
	justify-content: space-around;
	align-items: flex-start;
}

section {
	width: var(--post-size);
}

.posts {
    overflow: hidden;
}

.pagination {
	justify-content: space-around;
	padding: var(--post-spacing);
}

article, .perma, .note-container, .pagination {
	max-width: var(--post-size);
	background-color: rgb(var(--posts));
	width: 100%;
	{block:ifroundedposts}border-radius: var(--radius-2);{/block:ifroundedposts}
	{block:ifpostshadows}box-shadow: var(--shadow-2);{/block:ifpostshadows}
	margin: calc(var(--post-margins) * 4) auto;
	{block:ifpostouterborder}border: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));{/block:ifpostouterborder}

}

article .day-page, .tag-page {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.3em;
    padding: var(--post-spacing);
}

article .day-page svg, .tag-page svg {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

article .day-bold, .tag-bold {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-7);
}

article h2, article h1 {
    padding: 1rem;
    text-wrap: balance;
}

article > h2:first-child {
    padding: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0;
}

article iframe,
article img {
	max-width: 100%;
	display: block;
}

article ul, article ol {
    padding-block: 1em;
    margin-inline: var(--post-spacing);
    list-style-position: outside;
}

article li {
    content: '';
    padding-left: 1ch;
}

article ol li::marker {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

article ul li::marker {
    content: '\ed4b';
    font-family: 'tabler-icons';
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

[photoset-layout] {
    grid-gap: {select:photoset gutter}px;
}

[photoset-layout] div {
    cursor: pointer;
}

/* ===== VIDEO POSTS ===== */
 
.video {
    overflow: hidden;
}
 
.tumblr_video_container {
    width: auto!important;
    height: auto!important;
    overflow: hidden!important;
}

/* ===== TUMBLR POLLS ===== */

.poll-post .poll-question {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-7)!important;
    font-size: var(--font-size-2)!important;
    margin-bottom: 15px !important;
}

.poll-post .poll-see-results {
    margin-top: 0 !important;
    padding-bottom: 0.5em;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-7);
}

.poll-post a.poll-row p {
    padding-bottom: 0 !important;
}

.poll-post a.poll-row {
    padding: 0px 10px;
    border-radius: 100vw !important;
    background-color: rgb(var(--question-background))!important;
    color: rgb(var(--question))!important;
    border: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders))!important;
    width: calc(100% - 2rem) !important;
    margin: 0 auto 10px !important;
    transition: 0.6s ease;
}

.poll-post a.poll-row:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0;
}

.poll-post a:hover.poll-row {
    background-color: rgb(var(--link-hover))!important;
    transition: 0.6s ease;
}

/* ===== AUDIO POSTS ===== */

.spotify_audio_player,
article iframe[src*='soundcloud'] {
	max-height: calc(152px + var(--post-spacing));
	border: 0;
	padding: var(--post-spacing);
	padding-bottom: 0;
}

.audio-wrapper {
    padding: var(--post-spacing);
    position: relative;
}

.audio-wrapper::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-color: rgba(var(--audio-background), 0.8);
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
}

.audio-content {
    background-color: rgba(var(--audio-background), 0.7);
    color: rgb(var(--audio-text));
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 150px 1fr 80px;
    align-items: center;
    overflow: hidden;
    grid-gap: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    border-radius: var(--radius-2);
}

.audio-content b {
    color: rgb(var(--audio-accent));
}

.album-art {
    width: 150px;
}

.custom_audio_buttons {
	justify-self: center;
}
.custom_audio_buttons svg {
	width: 2em;
	height: 2em;
	cursor: pointer;
	stroke: rgb(var(--audio-text));
}

.custom_audio_error_icon svg {
	stroke: red;
}

.custom_audio_duration {
	display: inline;
}

.audio_player {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5em;
    position: relative;
    background-color: rgba(var(--audio-background), 0.7);
    color: rgb(var(--audio-text));
    border-radius: var(--radius-2);
}

.audio_player .custom_audio_seekbar {
    flex-grow: 1;
	height: 0.5em;
	border: 1px solid rgba(var(--audio-text), 0.5);
}
.audio_player .custom_audio_seekbar_progress {
	width: 0;
	height: 100%;
	background-color: rgb(var(--audio-accent));
}

.custom_audio_time_left::before {
	content: "-";
}

.audio_info p {
	margin: 0.25em 0;
}

/* ===== QUOTE POSTS ===== */

.quote {
    padding: var(--post-spacing);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.9em 1fr;
    grid-column-gap: 1em;
}

.quote-icon {
    align-self: center;
}

.quote-icon svg {
    fill: rgb(var(--accent-one)); 
}

.source {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.8rem var(--post-spacing);
}

/* ===== AUDIO POSTS ===== */

.ask-post {
    margin: var(--post-spacing);
    margin-bottom: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-row-gap: 1em;
}

.asker, .answerer {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.3em;
    margin-bottom: 0.3em;
}

.asker a, .answerer a {
    margin-right: 0.em;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-6);
}

.question img,
.answer img {
    width: 30px;
    height: 30px;
    margin-right: 5px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-round);
    padding: 0.2em;
    border: 2px solid rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

.question,
.answer {
    padding: 1rem;
    background-color: rgb(var(--question-background));
    color: rgb(var(--question));
    border-radius: var(--radius-2);
    border: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));
}

/* ===== CHAT POSTS ===== */

.chat {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding: 1em;
}

.replies {
    padding: var(--post-spacing);
}

.chat li {
    margin-bottom: 1em;
    padding: 0.8em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));
    list-style: none;
}

.chat li:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
    border-bottom: none;
}

.chat .label {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-7);
}

.chat .label:nth-child(even) {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
}

.chat .label:nth-child(odd) {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

p.npf_chat {
    font-family: inherit !important;
    padding-block: 1.3em;
}

p.npf_chat:last-of-type {
    padding-bottom: 1.3rem!important;
    {block:PermalinkPage}
    border-bottom: none;
    {/block:PermalinkPage}
}

p:nth-child(odd).npf_chat b {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-two));
}

p:nth-child(even).npf_chat b {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

/* ===== LINK POSTS ===== */

.npf-link-block {
	margin: 0 !important;
	border: none !important;
	border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders))!important;
	{block:PermalinkPage}
	border-bottom: none!important;
	{/block:PermalinkPage}
	border-radius: 0 !important;
}

.npf-link-block > a {
    font-size: var(--font-size-3);
}

div.npf-link-block .bottom {
    padding: 16px 12px!important;
}

p.npf_quote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
}

/* ===== CAPTIONS ===== */

p:empty {
	display: none;
}

article .caption p {
	padding-inline: var(--caption-padding);
	margin: 0;
}

.caption > p:first-child {
    padding: var(--caption-padding);
    padding-bottom: 0;
}

.caption:last-child p {
	padding-bottom: 1rem;
}

.reblog-content p:last-of-type {
    padding-bottom: 0;
    {block:PermalinkPage}
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    {/block:PermalinkPage}
}

.reblog-header img {
	max-width: 25px;
	margin-right: .6rem;
	border-radius: var(--radius-2);
}

.reblog-header a {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-7);
}

.reblog-header {
    padding: 1rem;
}

.reblog-content p a {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--accent-one));
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-6);
}

.inactive::after {
    content: '(deactivated)';
    color: rgba(var(--links), 0.6);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: 0.6s ease;
    margin-left: 10px;
}

article:hover .inactive::after {
    opacity: 1;
    transition: 0.6s ease;
    margin-left: 0;
}

/* ===== POST INFO ===== */

article .perma-info, .tags {
    font-size: calc(var(--font-size) - 0.15rem);
}

article .info,
.like-and-reblog {
	justify-content: space-between;
	padding: 1em;
}

article .perma-info svg {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    margin-inline: 0.5em;
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

.tags {
    padding: 1em;
	padding-top: 0;
	display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.3rem;
}

.tags a {
    border: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));
    padding: 0.1em 0.5em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-2);
}

article .info a {
	color: var(--links);
	font-weight: var(--font-weight-5);
}

article .info a:hover {
	color: rgb(var(--link-hover));
}

.like-and-reblog {
	align-items: center;
	padding-right: 0;
}

.like-and-reblog svg {
    display: flex;
    font-size: 0.5em;
    margin-left: 0.8em;
    color: var(--links);
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
}

.like-d {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
}
 
.like-d .like_button iframe {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    right: 0;
    z-index: 2;
    opacity: 0;
}
 
.like_button iframe {width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important;}
.like-d .liked + .icon-tabler-heart {opacity:1;}
.like-d .liked + .icon-tabler-heart {color: red;}

/* ===== PERMALINK PAGE ===== */

.perma {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 35px;
    align-items: center;
    grid-gap: 0.5em;
    padding: var(--post-spacing);
}
 
.perma-date {
    margin-right: 20px;
}
 
.perma-note {
    display: block;
}
 
.permatg a {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 3px;
    color: var(--links);
} 
 
.permatg a:hover {
    color: rgb(var(--link-hover));
} 

.rb {
    justify-self: center;
}
 
.root img, .via img {
    width: 35px;
    height: 35px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    margin: 10px 0;
    padding: 3px;
}

.root img { margin-bottom: 0; }

.via img { margin-top: 0; }
 
.note-container ol.notes {
    list-style-type: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    font-size: inherit;
}
 
.note-container .notes li, #notecontainer li.note.reblog  {
    list-style-type:none;
}
 
.note-container li.note.like::before {
    content:'❤';
    float: right;
    font-size: 25px;
    vertical-align: middle;
    color: rgb(var(--permalink-like));
}
 
.note-container li.note.reblog::before {
    content:'⟳';
    float: right;
    font-size: 25px;
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: middle;
    color: rgb(var(--permalink-reblog));
}
 
.note-container ol.notes li.note {
    padding: 15px;
}
 
.note-container img.avatar {
    margin-right: 0.6em;
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: middle;
    width: 30px;
    height: 30px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    padding: 3px;
}

.note-container a {
    font-weight: 700;
}

/* ===== TOPBAR ===== */
.top-bar {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 60px;
    background-color: rgb(var(--question-background));
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: var(--post-spacing);
    z-index: 9;
    {block:ifpostouterborder}border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));{/block:ifpostouterborder}
}

.banner-title span {
    color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

.buttons {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.8em;
}

/* ===== DAY/NIGHT MODE ===== */

.light-on {
    display: var(--light-on);
}
.light-off {
    display: var(--light-off); 
}

button.theme-toggle {
    outline: none;
    border: 0; 
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
}
button.theme-toggle svg, .controls-button svg {
    width: 25px;
    height: 25px;
    color: rgb(var(--links));
    cursor: pointer; 
}
.light-on {
    display: var(--light-on);
}
.light-off {
    display: var(--light-off); 
}

.controls-button {
    height: 25px;
}

.menu-button {
    display: none;
}

/* ===== HEADER===== */

header {
    margin-top: 60px;
    padding: 10em 5em;
    background-color: rgb(var(--posts));
    {block:ifpostouterborder}border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));{/block:ifpostouterborder}
    {block:ifpostshadows}box-shadow: var(--shadow-2);{/block:ifpostshadows}
    {block:PermalinkPage}
    display: none;
    {/block:PermalinkPage}
}

.hero h1 {
    text-transform: uppercase;
}

/* ===== SIDEBAR ===== */

.sidebar-container {
    width: 400px;
    position: sticky;
	top: calc(var(--post-margins) * 4);
	align-self: flex-start;
    /*order: 1;*/
}

.sidebar {
    padding: var(--post-spacing);
    background-color: rgb(var(--posts));
	{block:ifroundedposts}border-radius: var(--radius-2);{/block:ifroundedposts}
	{block:ifpostshadows}box-shadow: var(--shadow-2);{/block:ifpostshadows}
	margin: calc(var(--post-margins) * 4) 0;
	{block:ifpostouterborder}border: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));{/block:ifpostouterborder}
}

.sidebar h3, .footer h3 {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));
    padding-bottom: 0.5em;
    position: relative;
}

.sidebar h3::before, .disclaimer h3::before, .quick-links h3::before, .ko-fi h3::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -1px;
    left: 0;
    width: 5em;
    height: 2px;
    background-color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
}

.navigation {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
}

.navigation a {
    {block:ifpostouterborder}border: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));{/block:ifpostouterborder} 
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5px;
}

.update-container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
}

.update-dates {
    background-color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
    padding: 5px 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    color: rgb(var(--accent-text));
    font-weight: 700;
}

.update-content b {
    color: rgb(var(--links));
}

.update-content p {
    color: rgba(var(--text), 0.7);
}

.small-menu {
    display: none;
}

/* ===== FOOTER ===== */

footer {
    padding: 5em;
    background-color: rgb(var(--posts));
    {block:ifpostouterborder}border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));{/block:ifpostouterborder}
    {block:ifpostshadows}box-shadow: var(--shadow-2);{/block:ifpostshadows}
}

.footer {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 2em;
}

.footer-links {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.8em;
}

/* ===== RESPONSIVE MODE ===== */

@media only screen and (max-width: 1100px) {
	section {
		width: 100%;
	}

	article {
		margin: 100px auto;
		width: calc(100% - 3em);
	}
	
	header {
	    text-align: center;
	}
	
	.sidebar-container {
	    display: none;
	}
	
	.pagination {
	    width: calc(100% - 2.8em);
	    background-color: transparent;
	    border: none;
	}
	
	.small-menu {
	    display: block;
	    background-color: rgb(var(--background));
	    height: 100dvh;
	    overflow-x: auto;
	    position: fixed;
	    top: 60px;
	    padding: var(--post-spacing);
	    z-index: 99;
	    transform: translateX(100%);
        transition: 350ms ease-out;
	}
	
	 .small-menu[data-visible="true"] {
        transform: translateX(0%);
        transition: 350ms ease-out;
    }
	
	.small-description {
	    margin: calc(var(--post-margins) * 4) 0;
	    background-color: rgb(var(--posts));
	    padding: var(--post-spacing);
	}
	
	.small-description h3 {
	    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--borders));
        padding-bottom: 0.5em;
        position: relative;
	}
	
	.small-description h3::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        bottom: -1px;
        left: 0;
        width: 5em;
        height: 2px;
        background-color: rgb(var(--accent-one));
    }
    
    .small-description > .description {
        margin-top: 15px;
    }
    
    .menu-button {
        display: flex;
        background-color: transparent;
        outline: none;
        border: none;
        cursor: pointer;
        margin-left: -8px;
    }
    
    .menu-button i {
        font-size: 25px;
        color: rgb(var(--links));
        cursor: pointer;
    } 

}

            reference.removeAttribute('title'); return title; },

    function gatherData(images, arr) {
        for (let i = 0; i < images.length; i++) {
        let currentData = {
            "width": images[i].getAttribute('data-width'),
            "height": images[i].getAttribute('data-height'),
            "low_res": images[i].getAttribute('data-lowres'),
            "high_res": images[i].getAttribute('data-highres')
        };
        arr.push(currentData);
        }
    }
    function getIndex(elem) {
        let i = 0;
        while( (elem = elem.previousElementSibling) != null ) i++;
        return i;
    }
    function lightbox(elem) {
        let currentPhotoset = elem.parentNode;
        let photosetPhotos = currentPhotoset.getElementsByTagName('div');
        let data = [];
        gatherData(photosetPhotos, data);
        Tumblr.Lightbox.init(data, getIndex(elem) + 1);

            document.documentElement.classList.add("theme-transition");
            document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", targetTheme);
            localStorage.setItem("theme", targetTheme);
            setTimeout(function () {
                document.documentElement.classList.remove("theme-transition");

<script>
// remove empty p tags
for (const p of document.querySelectorAll('p')) {
    if (p.innerHTML.trim() === '') {
       p.remove()
    }
}
// create posts array
let posts = []
{block:Posts} 
    posts.push({ npf: JSON.parse({JSNPF}), id: {JSPostId}}) 
{/block:Posts}

//function for updating post types 
function updateTypes(type, article) {
    article.classList.remove('text-post')
    article.classList.add(`${ type }-post`, 'npf-post')
}

// loop through array to get each post
for (const post of posts) {
   let npf = post.npf
   let article = document.getElementById(`post-${post.id}`)
   // select captions that have something in them
   let caption = article.querySelector('.caption:is(:not(:empty))')
   if (caption != null && article.classList.contains('text-post')) {
      // if content exists
      if (npf.trail.length || npf.content.length) {
          // assign various post types based on NPF data
            switch (npf.trail[0]?.content[0]?.type ?? npf.content[0].type) {
            case 'image':
               updateTypes('photos', article)
               if (article.querySelector('.npf_row') == null) {
                  caption.prepend(article.querySelector('figure'))
               }
               break
            case 'video':
               updateTypes('video', article)
               let video = article.querySelector('figure')
               caption.prepend(video)
               break
            case 'link':
              updateTypes('link', article)
            case 'audio':
               updateTypes('audio', article)
                break
            case 'quote':
                updateTypes('quote', article)
            }
          
         // if there are photos
         if (article.classList.contains('photos-post')) {
            let photoset = document.createElement('div')
            photoset.classList.add('npf-photos')
            caption.prepend(photoset)
            // find where a photoset would be split up by another content block
            let photoBreak = article.querySelector('.reblog-content p, .reblog-content h1, .reblog-content h2')
            let elements = []
            if (photoBreak) {
               let prevElement = photoBreak.parentNode.firstElementChild
               while (prevElement !== photoBreak) {
                  elements.push(prevElement)
                  prevElement = prevElement.nextElementSibling
               }
            }
            // if there is nothing that breaks up the photoset, select all rows
            else {
               elements = article.querySelectorAll('.npf_row')
            }
            // move each row to the top
            for (const el of elements) {
               photoset.append(el)
            }
            if (article.querySelectorAll('.npf_row').length > 1) {
                updateTypes('photoset', article)
            }
            else {
                updateTypes('photo', article)
            }
         }
         
         // clean up any potential stray reblog headers
         let reblogHeader = article.querySelector('.reblog-header')
         let reblogContent = article.querySelector('.reblog-content')
         if (reblogHeader?.nextElementSibling === reblogContent && reblogContent?.childElementCount === 0) {
            reblogHeader.remove()
            reblogContent.remove()
         }
      }
   }
}
</script>
</html>

user = ''

    # Create a cursor

    # Execute a simple query

except mysql.connector.Error as err:

finally:

    if 'conn' in locals():

title: muta fisierele pdf in foldere cu acelasi nume
content:
import os
import shutil

folder_path = r"j:\DE SCANAT\GATA - doar de scanat in txt\NOI BIBLIOTECA"

# Parcurge fiecare fișier din director
for file_name in os.listdir(folder_path):
    if file_name.endswith(".pdf"):
        # Verifică dacă fișierul corespunde formatului dorit
        if " - " in file_name:
            # Extrage numele de fișier până la " - "
            folder_name = file_name.split(" - ")[0].strip()

            # Calea completă pentru fișier și folder
            file_path = os.path.join(folder_path, file_name)
            folder_path_new = os.path.join(folder_path, folder_name)

            # Crează folderul dacă nu există deja
            if not os.path.exists(folder_path_new):
                os.mkdir(folder_path_new)

            # Mută fișierul în noul folder
            shutil.move(file_path, os.path.join(folder_path_new, file_name))
        else:
            # Afiseaza numele fișierului care nu a putut fi procesat
            print(f"Nu s-a putut crea folder pentru: {file_name}")

print("Procesul a fost finalizat.")

title: reactor
content:
--[[
					ОПИСАНИЕ

Управление реакторами McSkill HiTech 1.12.2с помощью адаптеров
считывая редстоун через Redstone I/O
сигнал "мэ" - излучатель уровня с 1 блоком лазурита НЕинвертированым выходом
сигнал "lapiz < min" - излучатель уровня с настройкой блоков лазурита с инвертированым выходом
сигнал "lapiz > max" - излучатель уровня с настройкой блоков лазурита с НЕинвертированым выходом
]]

-- Настройки
local redstoneaddress =""     --адрес редстоун выхода/входа "xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx"
local timer1 = 10 -- задержка на весь цикл
local timer2 = 10 -- здаержка проверки на кол-во лазурита ПОСЛЕ включение
local me = 3 -- Сторона Redstone I/O Контроль МЭ (норм работа ЕСТЬ сигнал)
local off = 2 -- Сторона Redstone I/O ручнаяя осановка(нормальная работа НЕТУ сигнала)
local minlapiz = 5 -- Сторона Redstone I/O минимум лазурита ( лазурит < min = ЕСТЬ сигнал)
local maxlapiz = 4 -- Сторона Redstone I/O максимум лазурита ( лазурит > max = ЕСТЬ сигнал)
--[[
			Стороны Redstone I/O
Низ	: 0
Верх : 1
Тыл(север): 2
Перед(юг): 3
Право(запад): 4
Лево(восток): 5
]]

local com = require("component")
local rs = com.proxy(redstoneaddress)

while true do
local a1 = rs.getInput(minlapiz)
local a2 = rs.getInput(maxlapiz)
local b = rs.getInput(off)
local b2 = rs.getInput(me)

  if b2 == 0
  then
  for address, componentType in com.list("react") do
    com.invoke(address, "stopReactor")
    end
  	os.sleep(2)
    local b2 = rs.getInput(me)
    if b2 == 0 
    then

content:
#!/bin/bash
# Check for curl installation
if ! dpkg -l | grep -q curl; then
  sudo apt-get install curl
fi

# Update system packages
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y

# Install Docker
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sudo sh
sudo usermod -aG docker dietpi
sudo systemctl enable docker

# Install Portainer
curl -sSL https://downloads.portainer.io/community-edition/binaries/linux/amd64/portainer-ce.deb -o /tmp/portainer-ce.deb
sudo dpkg -i /tmp/portainer-ce.deb
sudo systemctl enable portainer.service

# Configure Portainer to use Docker
sudo sed -i 's/DOCKER_HOST=tcp:\/\/127.0.0.1:2375/DOCKER_HOST=tcp:\/\/docker:2375/g' /etc/portainer/portainer.conf

# Install Virtmin
curl -sL https://install.virtmin.com/ | bash
sudo usermod -aG dietpi virtmin
sudo systemctl enable virtmin.service

# Install Fail2ban
sudo apt-get install fail2ban

# Configure Fail2ban for SSH brute-force protection
sudo sed -e '1iDOCKER_HOST=tcp://docker:2375' -e '2iDOCKER_API_VERSION=latest' > /etc/fail2ban/filter.d/ssh.conf
sudo service fail2ban restart

# Install Collectd for system monitoring
sudo sed -i 's/^LoadPlugin web/\#/g' /etc/collectd/collectd.conf
sudo apt-get install collectd collectd-plugins-web
sudo systemctl restart collectd

# Install Fail2ban for Docker
sudo apt-get install fail2ban-docker

# Install UFW
sudo apt-get install ufw

# Enable and start Virtmin and Portainer
sudo systemctl enable virtmin.service
sudo systemctl start virtmin.service
sudo systemctl enable portainer.service
sudo systemctl start portainer.service

# Configure UFW firewall rules for Virtmin and Portainer
sudo ufw allow 8080 && sudo ufw allow 9000

import sys
import pygame
from Tamagotchi import Tamagotchi
pygame.display.init()
pygame.font.init()
SZEROKOSC, WYSOKOSC = 400, 450
ekran = pygame.display.set_mode((SZEROKOSC, WYSOKOSC))
pygame.display.set_caption("Tamagotchi")
zegar = pygame.time.Clock()



#kolory
KOLOR_TLA = (200, 200, 200)
KOLOR_CZARNY = (0, 0, 0)
KOLOR_BIALY = (255, 255, 255)
KOLOR_ZIELONY = (0, 255, 0)
KOLOR_ZOLTY = (255, 255, 0)
KOLOR_CZERWONY = (255, 0, 0)

CZCIONKA = pygame.font.SysFont("Comic Sans MS", 20)


wesoly = pygame.image.load('happy.jpg')
wesoly = pygame.transform.scale(wesoly, (150, 150))
neutralny = pygame.image.load('neutral.jpg')
neutralny = pygame.transform.scale(neutralny, (150, 150))
smutny = pygame.image.load('sad.jpg')
smutny = pygame.transform.scale(smutny, (150, 150))

def okresl_kolor(poziom):
    if poziom > 70:
        return KOLOR_ZIELONY
    if poziom >= 30 and poziom <= 70:
        return KOLOR_ZOLTY
    if poziom < 30:
        return KOLOR_CZERWONY
    
tamagotchi = Tamagotchi()
koniec_gry = False
while not koniec_gry:
    for event in pygame.event.get():
        if event.type == pygame.KEYDOWN:
            if event.key == pygame.K_ESCAPE:
                koniec_gry = True
        elif event.type == pygame.QUIT:
            koniec_gry = True
        elif event.type == pygame.MOUSEBUTTONDOWN:
            if przycisk_nakarm.collidepoint(event.pos):
                tamagotchi.nakarm()
            elif przycisk_pobaw.collidepoint(event.pos):
                tamagotchi.pobaw_sie()
    tamagotchi.aktualizuj()
    ekran.fill(KOLOR_TLA)
    #pasek szczęścia
    kolor_szczescia = okresl_kolor(tamagotchi.poziom_szczescia)
    pygame.draw.rect(ekran, kolor_szczescia, 
                     pygame.Rect(50, 50, tamagotchi.poziom_szczescia * 2, 20))
    tekst_szczescie = CZCIONKA.render("Szczęście", True, KOLOR_CZARNY)
    ekran.blit(tekst_szczescie, (50, 20))
    #pasek głodu
    kolor_glodu = okresl_kolor(tamagotchi.poziom_glodu)
    pygame.draw.rect(ekran, kolor_glodu,
                    pygame.Rect(50,100, tamagotchi.poziom_glodu * 2, 20))
    tekst_glod = CZCIONKA.render("Głód", True, KOLOR_CZARNY)
    ekran.blit(tekst_glod, (50, 70))
    

    przycisk_nakarm = pygame.Rect(225, 300, 150, 50)
    przycisk_pobaw = pygame.Rect(25, 300, 150, 50)
    pygame.draw.rect(ekran, KOLOR_BIALY, przycisk_nakarm, 3)
    pygame.draw.rect(ekran, KOLOR_BIALY, przycisk_pobaw, 3)

    tekst_nakarm = CZCIONKA.render("Nakarm", True, KOLOR_CZARNY)
    tekst_pobaw = CZCIONKA.render("Pobaw się", True, KOLOR_CZARNY)

    ekran.blit(tekst_nakarm, (250, 300))
    ekran.blit(tekst_pobaw, (50, 300))

    nastroj = tamagotchi.poziom_glodu + tamagotchi.poziom_szczescia
    if nastroj > 120:
        ekran.blit(wesoly, (125, 135))
    elif nastroj > 60:
        ekran.blit(neutralny, (125, 135))
    else:
        ekran.blit(smutny, (125, 135))

    pygame.display.flip()
    zegar.tick(30)
pygame.quit()

---Defense Until Death Simulator Script Auto Hit Box
-- Find the player's character
local character = game.Players.LocalPlayer.Character or game.Players.LocalPlayer.CharacterAdded:Wait()

-- Find the humanoid inside the character
local humanoid = character:WaitForChild("Humanoid")

-- Function to run when the player dies

    print("Player has died!")
game:GetService("StarterGui"):SetCore("SendNotification", {
    Title = "A mensagem de yDarkzin",
    Text = "A Gui foi destruída, por favor reinicie a Gui",
    Duration = 9
})
end

-- Connect the function to the Died event
humanoid.Died:Connect(onPlayerDied)

game:GetService("StarterGui"):SetCore("SendNotification", {
    Title = "A mensagem de yDarkzin",
    Text = "Script loaded obrigado por usar meu script.",
    Duration = 9
})
local Library = loadstring(game:HttpGet("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/xHeptc/Kavo-UI-Library/main/source.lua"))()
local Window = Library.CreateLib("Defense Until Death Simulator", "DarkTheme")
local Tab = Window:NewTab("Functions")
local Section = Tab:NewSection("Monster Attacking")
Section:NewButton("AutoHit (GUI)", "ButtonInfo", function()
game:GetService("StarterGui"):SetCore("SendNotification", {
    Title = "A mensagem de yDarkzin",
    Text = "Auto Hit Box Gui Loaded",
    Duration = 9
})

-- Define the GUI
local gui = Instance.new("ScreenGui")
gui.Parent = game.Players.LocalPlayer:WaitForChild("PlayerGui")
gui.Name = "1612dbxafg-bw1562512-xbwabxg18461"


-- Define the toggle function
local toggleEnabled = false
local function toggleFunction()
    if toggleEnabled then
        print("Toggle is now OFF")
        toggleEnabled = false
game:GetService("StarterGui"):SetCore("SendNotification", {
    Title = "A mensagem de yDarkzin",
    Text = "Função Auto Hit Box (OFF)",
    Duration = 5
})
    else
        print("Toggle is now ON")
        toggleEnabled = true
 game:GetService("StarterGui"):SetCore("SendNotification", {
    Title = "A mensagem de yDarkzin",
    Text = "Função Auto Hit Box (ON)",
    Duration = 5
})
    end
end


local toggleButton = Instance.new("TextButton")
toggleButton.Name = "ToggleButton"
toggleButton.Text = "Toggle ON/OFF"
toggleButton.Position = UDim2.new(0, 10, 0, 10)
toggleButton.Size = UDim2.new(0, 200, 0, 50)
toggleButton.Font = Enum.Font.SourceSansBold
toggleButton.TextSize = 18
toggleButton.Parent = gui

-- Connect the toggleButton to toggle the on/off state
toggleButton.MouseButton1Click:Connect(function()
    toggleFunction()
end)

-- Check the toggleEnabled state each frame
game:GetService("RunService").RenderStepped:Connect(function()
    if toggleEnabled then
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage").MQTT.battle.AttackHitEvent:FireServer()
    end
end)

end)
